The paper discusses the use of publication and citation data to compare the research performance of Innovation Studies units and Business & Management schools, which suggests a focus on digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The study also examines the degree of interdisciplinarity, which could be relevant to cybernetics (cs.CY) and security and privacy (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper discusses the bias in journal rankings, which could be relevant to social and information networks (cs.SI).
